Third-party dependency note (not part of the MIT license above):

The analysis code in this directory imports third-party Python libraries that
are not distributed with this repository and must be installed separately by
the user. Most of these (numpy, pandas, scipy, seaborn, statsmodels, and
matplotlib) are released under permissive BSD-style licenses. One dependency,
pingouin (https://pingouin-stats.org/), is licensed under the GPL-3.0.

Because this repository distributes only its own MIT-licensed source code and
does not bundle or redistribute pingouin, the MIT license above applies to the
code as written. Users who install and run the code are responsible for
complying with the licenses of the third-party libraries they install.
